e (Embryoscope and Miri-TL incubators. Software analysis for both incubators).</li>\r\n 	<li>Training and teaching IVF lab procedures for students and newly employed biologists.</li>\r\n 	<li>Andrology: Semen analysis, Anti sperm antibodies, sperm preparations and related testing.</li>\r\n 	<li>Embryology: Oocytes maturity grading, In vitro Fertilization and embryo transfer and related procedures.</li>\r\n 	<li>Oocyte and blastocyst vitrification.</li>\r\n 	<li>Embryo biopsy at day 3 and blastocyst stage. Blastomere fixation.</li>\r\n 	<li>Meiotic spindle identification by using the Spindleview™ Imaging System.</li>\r\n 	<li>Oocyte and embryo micromanipulation: Intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI) and assisted hatching (AH).</li>\r\n 	<li>Micro-Epididymal Sperm Aspiration (MESA) and Testicular Sperm Extraction (TESE).</li>\r\n 	<li>Extended culture to blastocyst stage using sequential as well as co-culture systems.</li>\r\n 	<li>Sperm and embryo freezing and thawing techniques.</li>\r\n 	<li>Statistics and data processing.</li>\r\n 	<li>QC/QA.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><u> </u></em>\r\n\r\n<em><u>Clinical (Research)</u></em><em><u> </u></em>\r\n\r\nMy PhD position was focusing in improving the efficiency of human oocyte  in vitro maturation (IVM) by performing a research study in healthy female volunteers/ PCO patients:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Responsible embryologist of the clinical IVM program, under my supervision I had 4 technicians – embryologist at Centrum voor Reproductieve Geneeskunde. Universitair Ziekenhuis Brussel (UZ Brussel).</li>\r\n 	<li>Developing a novel IVM culture system, in collaboration with COOK<sup>©</sup></li>\r\n 	<li>Testing and examining additives in oocyte maturation culture system for immature oocytes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Examining gene expression pattern in cumulus cells, matured oocytes and embryos after IVM (PCR).</li>\r\n 	<li>Oocyte and blastocyst vitrification.</li>\r\n 	<li>Intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI) for the mature oocyte after IVM.</li>\r\n 	<li>Embryo culture &amp; development assessment.</li>\r\n 	<li>Preimplantational genetic screening (PGS) of IVM oocytes and blastocysts by array comparative genomic hybridization (aCGH).</li>\r\n 	<li>PGD by fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) (PGD/FlSH) for embryos and blastocysts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><u>Basic oocyte biology &amp; embryology (Research)</u></em>\r\n\r\nThe following procedures and skilled were gained throughout my studies (PhD degree): my project was focusing in improving the efficiency of oocyte maturation in vitro in human.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Testing and examining additives in human oocyte maturation culture system.</li>\r\n 	<li>Oocyte retrieval, handling and culture.</li>\r\n 	<li>Embryology: IVF &amp; embryo culture &amp; evaluation.</li>\r\n 	<li>Radio Immuno Assay (RIA).</li>\r\n 	<li>Animal housing &amp; breeding colony care.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Certifications</u></strong><strong><u> </u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Clinical Embryologist. European Society of Human Reproduction and Embryology. 2011.</li>\r\n 	<li>PDG Technologist. Reprogenetics New Jersey. 2009. Pere Colls. Laboratory Director at Reprogenetics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><em><u> </u></em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em><u>Professor</u></em></strong><u> </u>\r\n\r\nProgram for Embryologist Certification (PEC online) in Latin-American for the “Red Latinoamerica de Reproduccion Asistida” (REDLARA).\r\n\r\n<u> </u>\r\n\r\n<strong><em><u>Awards</u></em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>ASRM Corporate Member Council In-training Travel Award for the IFFS/ASRM 2013 meeting.</li>\r\n 	<li>Fellow for stage in “Instituto de Biotecnologia” – UNAM – Mexico. Macrouniversity of Latin-America and Caribian 2005.</li>\r\n 	<li>Fellow for Master Studies in Peruvian Universities. 2004-2005.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><em><u>Publications</u></em></strong><strong><em><u> </u></em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Inoue N, Lopez R, Delgado A, 